Preheat your oven to 200°C. Pour a glug of @oil{a glug} onto a #baking tray{} and pop in your oven. Bring a large #saucepan{} of @water{1000%ml}(with a pinch of @salt{}) to the boil on high heat. Peel the @potatoes{900%g}, chop them into 4cm chunks. Add the potatoes to the boiling water and cook for ~{7-8%minutes} or until the edges have softened when you poke them with a knife.

Meanwhile, halve the @echalion shallots{2} lengthways and peel. Trim and peel the @carrots{2}, quarter lengthways and chop widthways into small pieces.

Halve the @brussels sprouts{200%g}. Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove} (or use a #garlic press{}). Pick the @thyme{½} leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks).

Once the potatoes are ready, drain in a #colander{}, pop back into the pan then sprinkle on half the @plain flour{24%g}. Give your pan a shake to fluff up the potato. Take your hot baking tray out of your oven, carefully transfer your potatoes onto it in a single layer, turning in the oil. Season with @salt{}. Roast the potatoes on the top shelf of your oven for ~{45-50%minutes}, turn halfway through.

Keep the saucepan, we'll use it again later.

Crush the @black peppercorns{2} in a #freezer bag{} with the base of a saucepan and transfer them to a #plate{}. Roll the @British beef roasting joint{450%g} in the pepper, season with salt and a drizzle of oil, then transfer to a baking tray. Roast in the oven for ~{35%minutes} / ~{45%minutes} / ~{55%minutes} (depending on size) for medium rare. Add an extra ~{5%minutes} if you like your beef more cooked. Rest wrapped loosely in #foil{} for at least ~{10%minutes} before slicing.

Heat a splash of oil in a #frying pan{} over a medium-high heat. Add the shallots, cut side down and cook until browned, ~{3-4%minutes}.

In a #jug{}, stir the @chicken stock paste{½} into the @water{750%ml} for the shallots. Transfer the shallots to a small #ovenproof dish{}, sprinkle on half the thyme and pour on the stock. Pop on the bottom shelf of your oven and bake until soft and sweet, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Put a small saucepan on medium heat and add the @water{10000%ml} for the sauce, stir in the @red wine jus paste{1} and bring to a simmer.

When everything in the oven has 10 mins left, melt the @unsalted butter{30%g} in the saucepan you used for the potatoes over medium heat and add the carrots. Stir and cook until beginning to soften, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the brussels sprouts, garlic and remaining thyme, cook for ~{1%minute} and then add a splash of water. Cover with a #lid{} or foil and cook until the veggies are tender, another ~{5%minutes}.

Arrange the veggies on the plates and crumble over the @walnuts{20%g}. Add the roasties. Thinly slice the beef and arrange alongside. Pop the shallots on top of the beef and finish with the red wine jus. Enjoy!

== Festive Mulled Wine Spices ==

Peel the @lemon{1} and @orange{1} with a #potato peeler{}. Halve the orange and squeeze the juice into a large saucepan, add the lemon and orange peel, along with the @caster sugar{75%g}, @star anise{1}, @cardamom pod{1} and @cinnamon stick{1}. Pour over the @red wine{750%ml} and heat gently until the sugar has dissolved, stirring occasionally.

Bring to the boil, then remove from the heat and leave to infuse for ~{15%minutes} (or longer).

When ready to drink, warm it back up and pour into #mugs{} - Enjoy!

> It can also be stored in the fridge and reheated when you want it if you have any leftover.